<T>__{cut to bloom at the bar:}
<A>__{, frozen, staring straight ahead.}
<B>__{his eyes are glazed with shock. he strokes his cheek with his little blue blanket.}
<C>__{bloom}
<D>__{mrs. cathcart 50% mrs. biddlecombe 50% mrs. wentworth 50% mrs. resnick 100%}
<B>__{the drunk stares from one to the other. unhappy with their}
<A>__{present mood, he decides to liven things up again. he tiptoes over to bialystock, puts his arms around bialystock's waist, rocks back and forth and begins to sing.}
<C>__{drunk}
<P>__{(singing)}
<D>__{"by the light... by the light, by the light... of the silvery...}
<B>__{bialystock picks him up and throws him across the bar.}
<C>__{bialystock}
<D>__{get away from me, you drunken bum!}
<B>__{drunk picks himself up and dusts himself off.}
<C>__{drunk}
<P>__{(indignantly)}
<D>__{fairweather friend!}
<B>__{the drunk staggers out of the bar. bialystock gets a hold of himself.}
<C>__{bialystock}
<D>__{maybe it's not true!}
<B>__{bialystock rushes over to bloom.}
<C>__{bloom}
